.SH NAME
vmw_kms_atomic_check_modeset \- validate state object for modeset changes
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" vmw_kms_atomic_check_modeset
.BI "(struct drm_device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct drm_atomic_state *state "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
DRM device
.IP "state" 12
the driver state object
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is a simple wrapper around \fBdrm_atomic_helper_check_modeset\fP for
us to assign a value to mode->crtc_clock so that
\fBdrm_calc_timestamping_constants\fP won't throw an error message
.SH "RETURN"
Zero for success or -errno
